Introduction:
CardioCare is a web-based system designed to detect heart disease using machine learning algorithms and medical data analysis. The system aims to provide an accurate and timely diagnosis of heart disease, enabling healthcare professionals to take proactive measures and improve patient outcomes.

Problem Statement:
Heart disease is a leading cause of death worldwide, and early detection is crucial for effective treatment and prevention. Current diagnostic methods rely on manual analysis of medical data, which can be time-consuming and prone to errors. There is a need for an automated system that can accurately detect heart disease and provide timely alerts to healthcare professionals.

Objective:
Develop a web-based system to detect heart disease using machine learning algorithms and medical data analysis.

Scope:

- Frontend Scope:
    - Develop a user-friendly interface for users to input patient data and view diagnosis results
    - Display diagnosis results and provide recommendations for treatment
- Backend Scope:
    - Develop a machine learning model using algorithms (e.g., logistic regression, decision trees, random forest) to analyze medical data and detect heart disease
    - Train the model using publicly available datasets from GitHub (e.g., Cleveland Heart Disease Dataset)
    - Allow users to input patient data directly into the system for diagnosis
    - Develop a reporting module to generate comprehensive diagnosis reports

Methodology:
We will use an agile development approach, with iterative development and testing cycles. The project will be divided into sprints, with regular feedback and review.

Tools and Technology:

- Machine learning algorithms: logistic regression, decision trees, random forest
- Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React
- Backend: Python, Django
- Database: MySQL
- Data source: Cleveland Heart Disease Dataset from GitHub
- EHR integration: Not required (user-input data)

Expected Outcomes:

- A comprehensive web-based system for heart disease detection
- Accurate diagnosis of heart disease using machine learning algorithms
- Timely alerts and recommendations for treatment
- Improved patient outcomes and reduced mortality rates

Conclusion:
The CardioCare heart disease detection web system is a critical initiative to improve the diagnosis and treatment of heart disease. We believe that this system will provide an accurate and timely diagnosis, enabling healthcare professionals to take proactive measures and improve patient outcomes.
